es Eannes de Azurara]] (1899) translator with [[Edgar Prestage]] * An English Garner: Voyages and Travels mainly during the 16th and 17th Centuries (1902) two volumes * Voyages of the Elizabethan Seamen. Select Narratives from the 'Principal Navigations' of Hakluyt (1907) edited with [[Edward John Payne]] * A Note-book of Mediaeval History AD323–AD1453 (1917) * [http://catalog.hathitrust.org/Record/001601696 Russia From The Varangians To The Bolsheviks] (1918) with [[Nevill Forbes]] and [[G. A. Birkett]] * [http://catalog.hathitrust.org/Record/000398264 Nineteenth Century Europe] (1922) * The Road to Ruin in Europe (1932) * The Beauty of the North Cotswolds (1946)
